│ ### 4. Proposed Edit Point(s) ###                                                       │
│                                                                                         │
│ To fix this bug, I will add a check within                                              │
│ `ConstantOffsetExtractor::distributeExtsAndCloneChain`. Before attempting to distribute │
│ a `TruncInst` through an `AddOperator`, the code must verify that the `TruncInst` does  │
│ not have `nsw` or `nuw` flags. If either flag is present, the transformation must be    │
│ aborted for that instruction, and the original instruction `V` should be returned,      │
│ leaving the code unchanged.                                                             │
│                                                                                         │
│ The edit will be in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/SeparateConstOffsetFromGEP.cpp` inside  │
│ the `if (auto *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(Ext))` block, right at the beginning of the     │
│ block.                                                                                  │
│                                                                                         │
│ ```cpp                                                                                  │
│ // In ConstantOffsetExtractor::distributeExtsAndCloneChain at line 718                  │
│ if (auto *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(Ext)) {                                              │
│   // We can't do this if the trunc has nsw/nuw flags, because                           │
│   // trunc(add(X,C)) may be valid whereas trunc(X) is not.                              │
│   if (TI->hasNoSignedWrap() || TI->hasNoUnsignedWrap())                                 │
│     return V;                                                                           │
│   // ... rest of the logic                                                              │
│ }                                                                                       │
│ ```                                                                                     │
│                                                                                         │
│ This change ensures that the invalid transformation is no longer performed, fixing the  │
│ bug while preserving the optimization for cases where it is safe.                       │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 5. Conclusion ###                                                                   │
│                                                                                         │
│ The issue is a miscompilation caused by an incorrect transformation in the              │
│ `separate-const-offset-from-gep` pass that does not respect the semantics of            │
│ `nsw`/`nuw` flags on `trunc` instructions. The proposed fix is to add a guard to        │
│ prevent this transformation when these flags are present, which will resolve the bug    │
│ and ensure correctness.                                                                 │
