│ An LLVM bug in the `separate-const-offset-from-gep` pass is causing a miscompilation.   │
│ The pass incorrectly transforms `trunc nsw (add X, C)` into `add (trunc nsw X), C`,     │
│ which is an invalid transformation because the `nsw` (no signed wrap) property does not │
│ distribute over addition. This can lead to a valid operation being transformed into one │
│ that produces a poison value.                                                           │
│                                                                                         │
│ To fix this, I will modify the `ConstantOffsetExtractor::distributeExtsAndCloneChain`   │
│ function in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/SeparateConstOffsetFromGEP.cpp`. I will add a   │
│ check to ensure that this distribution does not occur if the `trunc` instruction has    │
│ `nsw` or `nuw` flags. This prevents the incorrect transformation while allowing it for  │
│ safe cases.                                                                             │
